features: Impressive Powerful Suction - The vacuum cleaners for home features 180W upgraded motor, provides strong suction on max mode, captures pet hair, cat litter, pet food, and other messes on the hardwood floor, low-pile carpet, stairs, bed, curtain, furniture, car, RV, etc. This vacuum cleaners for home generates less heat and less noise (65db) to offer a quiet cleaning environment.

45 Mins Runtime & 1.2 L Large Dustbin - The cordless vacuum cleaner is equipped with 6-Cell battery of 2200 m-A-h and a 1.2 L large dust cup. They work together to ensure one thorough cleaning of a whole house of 180㎡ (1937.50 sq ft) for 30-45 mins on standard mode, 15-20 mins on max mode . The battery is detachable and rechargeable, so you can charge either the stick vacuum integrated or the battery separated. With a 1.2L large dust cup, you can easily empty the dustbin with a one-button press.

Versatile Cleaning - Equipped with multiple accessories, including a 2-in-1 brush, long crevice, and extensible tube, this excellent cordless stick vacuum can meet various household cleaning demands on stairs and windowsills, sofa and bed, desk and curtain, cars, RV, etc. This lightweight vacuum cordless weighs only 3.2 lbs and supports self-standing, so you can start or stop whenever or wherever you want. Plus, wall mount storage can save you some space.

5 Stage High-Efficiency Filtration System - The 5-stage fully sealed cyclone filtration system is composed of a HEPA filter with a mesh filter, a stainless steel strainer, and cyclone separation. This stick vacuum cleaner cordless can efficiently capture 99.99% of the microscopic dust particles as small as 0.2 microns to avoid secondary pollution. It can provide ultimate purified air for your families, especially your babies.

Maneuverable Brush Head with 4 LEDs - Flexible 150°swivel sideways and 90°up and down lets you clean your home in all directions. 4 LED lights help vacuum cleaner cordless illuminate every dark area track dust and dirt.

INSE provides a 12-month warranty, accessories replacement, and 7*24 after-sale service for our valued customers, to enjoy a premium purchasing experience. Also, this stick vacuum cleaner is a nice gift for your parents, wife, and friends!

How long does it take to fully charge? When you get this vacuum, it only has about 30% battery power, before you first use it, please use the original adapter to charge for 4-5 hours fully. After fully charged, the vacuum will work up to 45 mins on standard mode, 15-20 mins on Max mode. What is the input voltage of the charger? Does it work on 220V? Yes. The power adapter of this N5T cordless vacuum ceaner can apply to 100-240V. The HEPA filter comes with a mesh wrap around it with a little blue tab. Do I leave that on or remove it before use? Please leave it on. When cleaning, you can remove the mesh wrap, and the mesh and steel drum can be washed with water. The HEPA filter should be cleaned dry with cleaning gadget. Ensure the filters are completely dry before refitting. What''s the difference between N5S and N5T ? The only difference is the battery, the battery of N5T is upgraded, both of the runtime is 40-45 mins on standard mode, 15-20 mins on Max mode. The battery of N5S and N5T cannot be universal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Bought this because I was sick of carrying my Hoover up and down the stairs. This vacuum works great, is easy and lightweight to carry. I have hardwood floors with several low pile rugs. This vacuum works great on both. It was worth the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very Nice Portable
reviews.reviewText: We used this for over a year and it works very well. Buy an extra battery fo sure as they lose charge in about 10 minutes on high speed. Does a good job of picking up dust, cat hair, dander and litter. BE SURE to clean off the filters after each battery discharge to keep suction strong and to keep from triggering the motor overheating safety that will reset when cooled.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Product is nice, but assembly …
reviews.reviewText: Product is very nice, quiet. But don’t expect help from the support line. They don’t know what they are doing, don’t know the product…say they will call back and don’t. I found help on u-tube for assembly. User manual is a joke. Like I said product is good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Light weight and easy to vacumn
reviews.reviewText: It is light weight, easy to set-up and picks up all the dirt !.. VERY HAPPY with RESULTS..salim

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Ok for black Friday sale, otherwise very overpriced
reviews.reviewText: I had a similar model that Amazon sold regularly for just $65.I figured this one, supposedly regularly priced at something like $450, would be much better (stronger suction), so I grabbed it on Black Friday sale for $99.But it's not. Only a slightly better suction, not even noticable until I did a ping pong ball test, and this one barely out performed the cheap $65 vacuum. I the test I turned both on high with a ping pong ball I the middle to see which would win by keeping the ball.So I guess it's worth it for the BF $99 proce, but definitely not a penny more.We also have a shark we bought at Sam's club, and that's tremendously more powerful.This is not in the same category as Shark, and certainly not Dyson. Just a cheap (at least once/year cheap) substitute. 😭

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good value for the price
reviews.reviewText: This does a great job for its size and weight. Can get into places that a larger vacuum couldn't. Assembly is a bit confusing, so read the manual over carefully when assembling it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars This vacuum sucks
reviews.reviewText: I have another $99 vacuum from Amazon that works so well but it was out of stock and I needed another vac for upstairs. This one is trash. The bottom head sticks up in the air and I have to kick it down every few seconds and when it is down it has terrible suction. You can find better. Trust.
